{"cursor":"5056","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n .]] The 'Gandhi\ncap' () is a white coloured sidecap, pointed in front and back and having a\nwide band. It is made out of [[khadi]]. It takes its name after the Indian\nleader Mahatma Gandhi, who first popularised its use during the Indian\nindependence movement. Worn commonly by Indian independence activists, it\nbecame a symbolic tradition for politicians and political activists to wear it\nin independent India.\n","linknr":227,"url":"Gandhi_cap","recorded":1362566517,"links":18,"instances":["cap"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Mohandas Karamchand Gandhi","Indian independence movement","Politics of India","Indian clothing","Hats","Caps","Indian headgear"],"headings":["Genesis","Post-independence","Re-emergence of the Gandhi cap","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/99/Question_book-new.svg/50px-Question_book-new.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e1/Nehru1920.jpg/220px-Nehru1920.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/4a/Commons-logo.svg/30px-Commons-logo.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["taqiyah","cap"]],"members":["taqiyah"],"related":["Sidecap","India","Mahatma_Gandhi","Indian_independence_movement","Indian_independence_activists","Gujarat","Uttar_Pradesh","Rajasthan","Bihar","West_Bengal","Maharashtra","Karnataka","Indian_National_Congress","Hindu_Mahasabha","Rashtriya_Swayamsevak_Sangh","Subhas_Chandra_Bose","Indian_National_Army","Jawaharlal_Nehru","Prime_Minister","Lal_Bahadur_Shastri","Morarji_Desai","Indian_Parliament","Republic","Anna_Hazare","Ramlila_Maidan","Middle_Class","Indian_National_Congress","Taqiyah_(cap)","S